  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Livelihood support for the very poor populations to strengthen their food security and nutrition in Senegal in 2014</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Targetting of very poor household beneficiaries based on socio-economic criterias (Household Economic Analysis - HEA); Unconditional cash transfers to 1 250 households over a 4 months period; Screening, monitoring and referencing of malnourished children; Dissemination and promotion of dietary and nutrition practices</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The  &quot;hunger gap&quot; came early in 2014 as a result of chronic vulnerability to food and nutrition insecurity in the Sahelian band and a poor agricultural season. ACTED-CECI supports 1 250 households in the department of Matam to support the very poor populations over a 4 months period. This support seeks to maintain beneficiary households&apos; food and nutrition security and to fill the hunger gap through unconditional cash transfers. Unconditional cash transfers are complemented by the screening, monitoring and referencing of malnourished children as well as awareness-raising sessions on essential family practices related to the improvement of households&apos; food and nutrition security, in particular of women and under-5 years old children&apos;s.</narrative>
  </description>
